title: Thailand jet-ski crash: Tom Keating confesses to charge of careless driving causing death: reports - Yahoo7
text:
Share Thailand jet-ski crash: Tom Keating confesses to charge of careless driving causing death: reports - Yahoo7 An Australian man whose girlfriend was tragically killed when their jet skis collided in Thailand has reportedly confessed to a charge of careless driving causing death. Close Tom Keating 'technically confesses' to jetski accident, 'not likely to do any jail time' UP NEXT VIDEO Thai police have formally charged aussie tourist Tom Keating over a jetski crash which killed his girlfriend. Source: 7 News Tom Keating 'technically confesses' to jetski accident, 'not likely to do any jail time' 
Thomas Keating arrived at a police station in Phuket on Thursday, flanked by members of his family along with the parents of the Victorian woman, Emily Collie, killed in the horror jet-ski crash. 
Police in Phuket told the ABC he pleaded guilty to the charge, however it’s expected he will be handed a suspended jail sentence meaning he would be free to return home in due course. Emily Collie and Tom Keating, before the fatal crash. Source: Facebook Mr Keating arrives at a Thailand police station, flanked by supporters from his family and Ms Collie's. Source: 7 News 
"Thomas pleaded guilty," Superintendent Sanya Thongsawad told the ABC. 
The ABC reported police said it was the first time Keating had ridden a jet ski. 
"Police don't have to detain him but he is now banned from leaving the country until the court process is completed," Superintendent Sanya told the ABC. 
Mr Keating had his passport confiscated on Thursday, meaning he cannot leave Thailand. Jet ski crash victim Emily Collie. Source: 7 News A devastated Tom Keating at the Phuket beach. Source: 7 News 
Mr Keating told local media after the incident he was blinded by the sunlight when his jet ski collided with his girlfriend’s. 
The heart-broken 22-year-old has already paid tribute to his late girlfriend in a touching Facebook post, where he said that he will “never be able to mend”. 
“I'll always be your boy and you'll always be my girl! We had so many plans for our future, Emmy," he said.
